		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">Bregalad wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">Though it would have an incorrect 2.54mm pitch 72 pin connector I believe.</div><br />I don't think it could work if such a connector is used. This would make more than half of a pin of difference with the error accumulating through all the connector.<br /><br />Yeah nintendo, non-standard PCB width, non-standard pin pitch. They are total assholes for this kind of stuff.</div><br /><br />I've used the wrong pitched 72 pin connector from Digikey going on two years now with heavy use and I love it.  Most people still don't believe me but It's works flawlessly.  The cart doesn't have enough clearance to slide back and forth enough to cause shorts/opens.  I've even tested a large number or unlicensed manufactures games and have yet to find an issue.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
